definition[0]: the amount of work, goods, or people that are dealt with in a particular period of time
example[0]: a large store with a high throughput of goods
example[1]: an airport with a weekly throughput of 100,000 passengers
definition[1]: the amount of work, materials etc that can be dealt with in a particular period of time
example[2]: The airport has a weekly throughput of 100,000 passengers.
example[3]: This machine has the throughput capacity of seven of our old computers  (=can deal with seven times as much information in the same period of time).
